			<section>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>DealTapp</strong></h3>
					<p>Connecting users with local businesses</p>
				</header>
				<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
					<p>DealTapp is an app that lets users to find the best deals at local restaurants, cafes, and entertainment venues. It gives power to small and local shops while making it easy for users to claim the offers.</p>
					<p>At DealTapp we have found success connecting with numerous local businesses and gathering users. Our success has been featured in tech blogs and articles. <a href="http://www.dailyuw.com/features/article_9884de00-05e4-11e6-a8c4-7be60332f7c9.html">UW newspaper article.</a></p>
				</div>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>Building a Company</strong></h3>
					</header>
					<div class="8u 12u$(medium)">
						<p>Being a part of a startup is an exciting thing. As the only designer for DealTapp, I helped create and continue to revise our product.</p>
						<p>I have a huge influence over the direction of the app and I get to wear many hats. Aside from my responsibilites as a UX Designer, I discuss decisions with the founders, take photographs, test the software, meet with newspaper reporters, and interview potential employees.</p>
						<p>I love being a part of this enviroment. I am always able to work on something new and gain new experiences. Being a part of a startup has taught me many things. For example, how I must adapt my design methods and know where to make cuts to fit the resources of the company.</p>
					</div>
				<header>
					<h3><strong>Building a Design Culture</strong></h3>
					</header>
				<div class="row">
					<div class="8u$ 12u$(medium)">
						<p>At DealTapp I want to build a culture that stresses good design. To do this I need to get the founders on board and show them the value of design. I first ran an initial round of user testing to gather concrete examples of usability problems. Then I created solutions to present to the founders.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</section>

